# Cloudflare Deploy Script Conventions

When implementing or updating `scripts/deploy-cloudflare.sh`, follow these rules:

## 1. Form URL Format

Forms are served at `/f/{id}`, not `/forms/{id}`.

- In deploy output, show: `Live URL: $WORKER_URL/f/$FORM_ID`
- The API returns `url: "/f/{id}"` from POST /api/forms

## 2. Upload-Only Mode

If `WORKER_URL` is set in the environment, skip the Worker deploy and only upload the form.

- Use case: Worker already deployed; user wants to retry form upload or upload another form
- Example: `WORKER_URL=https://formant.SUBDOMAIN.workers.dev bash scripts/deploy-cloudflare.sh forms/<name>.html`
- When skipping deploy, do not cd into the service package; stay in project root so paths resolve correctly

## 3. Working Directory

Before the form upload step (node -e and curl calls), ensure the current directory is the project root (`$ROOT_DIR`).

- After wrangler deploy (which runs from the service package), run `cd "$ROOT_DIR"` before building the request body and uploading
- This avoids path resolution issues when building the JSON payload

## 4. Error Handling

On form upload failure (HTTP non-2xx):

- Print the HTTP status code and response body
- Print a retry command: `WORKER_URL=$WORKER_URL bash scripts/deploy-cloudflare.sh $HTML_FILE`
- Exit with code 1

## 5. Wrangler Non-Interactive

- Use `wrangler deploy --yes` to avoid interactive prompts where possible
- workers.dev subdomain registration cannot be automated; if it is not registered, wrangler will fail
- Direct users to the Cloudflare dashboard onboarding URL when deploy fails

## Checklist for Deploy Script Changes

- [ ] Live URL uses `/f/$FORM_ID`, not `/forms/$FORM_ID`
- [ ] WORKER_URL env skips deploy when set
- [ ] `cd "$ROOT_DIR"` before the form upload step
- [ ] Upload failure prints the retry command with WORKER_URL
- [ ] `wrangler deploy --yes` is used for non-interactive deploy
